- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the definition of weak behavioural equivalences, which is a topic closely related to logic and semantics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the Kleisli categories of common monads, which are often used in programming language theory. 
- cs.LT (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with coalgebras, which are closely related to automata theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the complexity of behavioural equivalences. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the structure of categories and orders.
